Sentencas: Samarium strontium cobalt oxide with ABO(3) lattice structure, which is mixed ionic and electronic conductor (MIEC), is considered as a promising cathode material for intermediate temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC) due to its high electrocatalytic property.
Titulo: Characteristics of ABO3 and A2BO4 (A=Sm, Sr; B=Co, Fe, Ni) samarium oxide system as cathode materials for intermediate temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Cathode material containing cobalt (Co) is unstable at high temperature and has a relatively high thermal expansion coefficient.
Titulo: Characteristics of ABO3 and A2BO4 (A=Sm, Sr; B=Co, Fe, Ni) samarium oxide system as cathode materials for intermediate temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In this study, samarium oxide cathodes with ABO(3) and A(2)BO(4) (A=Sm, Sr; B=Co, Fe, Ni) structure on Sm(0.2)Ce(0.8)O(1.9) electrolyte were investigated in terms of electrochemical property and thermal expansion property.
Titulo: Characteristics of ABO3 and A2BO4 (A=Sm, Sr; B=Co, Fe, Ni) samarium oxide system as cathode materials for intermediate temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Area specific resistance (ASR) was measured by ac impedance spectroscopy, and thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) was measured using a dilatometer.
Titulo: Characteristics of ABO3 and A2BO4 (A=Sm, Sr; B=Co, Fe, Ni) samarium oxide system as cathode materials for intermediate temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Microstructure of cathode was observed using a scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Characteristics of ABO3 and A2BO4 (A=Sm, Sr; B=Co, Fe, Ni) samarium oxide system as cathode materials for intermediate temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Sm(0.5)Sr(0.5)CoO(3-delta) with ABO(3) structure showed the ASR of 0.87 Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C, and Sm(0.5)Sr(0.5)NiO(3 +/-delta), which actually has A(2)BO(4) structure, showed the lowest TEC value of 13.3 x 10(-6)/K. (C) 2007
Titulo: Characteristics of ABO3 and A2BO4 (A=Sm, Sr; B=Co, Fe, Ni) samarium oxide system as cathode materials for intermediate temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell
